review:
I used to dread dental visits after a harrowing root canal experience with a different dentist. 

Determined to avoid any more dental appointments, I endured months of increasing sensitivity and pain in my premolar teeth. Eventually, a sizable cavity emerged, signaling the urgent need for professional care.

Despite initial hesitation, I sought out Dr. Anupreet Kaur Choudhury in Kolkata, driven by her stellar reviews. On a Sunday, with heightened pain due to the cold weather, I discovered her clinic, impeccably clean and adhering to COVID protocols. Dr. Kaur's warm demeanor immediately eased my fears.

After explaining my dental woes, she conducted a thorough examination, revealing cavities and a misaligned wisdom tooth causing the pain. Despite my apprehensions from a past root canal, Dr. Kaur patiently addressed each query, explaining the necessary procedures and reassuring me. Encouraged by her confidence, I decided to proceed with a root canal.

To my surprise, the treatments were swift, spanning three sessions of 15-25 minutes each. Dr. Kaur, alongside Dr. Sumit and Dr. Gopal, exhibited expertise and care throughout, erasing my fears. The post-treatment phase was equally comforting, with no pain or discomfort, allowing me to resume normal eating habits.

In reflecting on this experience, I wholeheartedly recommend Dr. Kaur and her team to anyone seeking a reliable dentist. A heartfelt thank you to Dr. Anupreet Kaur Choudhury and her dedicated team for restoring my confidence in dental care.

review:
I visited Dr. Anupreet Kaur a few days ago for a consultation and possible treatment for recurring issues I've had due to an ongoing dental procedure (somewhere else), including two decayed wisdom teeth one of which had impacted a molar tooth beside it.
She carefully listened with a keen ear and meticulously provided planned solutions to the issues, which were taken care of by her and experienced doctors of her team at Dentall. 
I experienced painless extraction of the two decayed wisdom teeth in one sitting(by Dr. Basu, maxillofacial surgeon, Dentall) and minimal pain thereafter. I also underwent RCT for a molar tooth and it was painless(other than the minimal pain which is expected during the treatment).
Both the extraction and Root Canal Treatment were done very professionally. Dr. Kaur eased me well into them, by explaining everything involved during and after the procedures. Staff at Dentall have also been very cooperative and helpful throughout the course of days the procedures happened, responding to any query after the procedures. I also underwent removal of dental brackets and scaling, which were both done very proficiently by Dr. Anupreet without any pain or discomfort. 
I must add she is an amazing person with immense experience in her field and her dealing with patients is extremely professional, rare in today's world and highly commendable.

review: I went to Dr. Choudhary for my wisdom tooth extraction. She is very efficient in her work. The most important thing is she made me understand every detail of my problem and the treatment that she is going to do. This made me more confident about the treatment. I was always very sceptical about tooth extraction as I have heard from people that it's very painful process, that is the reason I had delayed my treatment thinking that the pain in my teeth will go automatically with time. The bleeding was also very less during extraction. Overall I am very very satisfied with her treatment. This experience completely took  away all the fear that I had about visiting a dentist. THANK YOU SO MUCH MA'AM ☺️☺️☺️☺️....Last but not the least the clinic is also very good, they follow all Covid guidelines ( sanitization processes etc.) , it's clean and hygienic.

review: As there are many dentists nearby i was very confused, where to go for consultation. so while searching through practo i found Dr Anupreet who is having 21 years experience and have nearly 100% recommendation,  which create a confidence in me to visit to her. I took a appointment through practo which was very simple and easy. while i visited the clinic, i was quite impressed to see all the sanitary protocols they are following, hence i felt very safe to visit there. During consultation, she understood my problems and advised  me for RCT of my teeth and as i gave my  consent, she started the 1st sitting immediately. ** ******** ** * ****** ******* ******** she did the whole 4 sittings of RCT within a week without having any pain in my teeth. I want to thank her very much and surely practo which helped me always to find a good doctor whenever i was in need. Thanks.

** **** ****** *** ******** ******* ** *** ****** ** ******** ** ***** ********* *** ***********
I visited Dentall clinic to seek advice regarding the possible options that could be adopted following the removal of a particular tooth on the lower right region (molar).
The concerned tooth was already damaged and required an extraction.
On the day of extraction, *** ****** ******* ****** **** * ******* that lasted 40 minutes and I was left to my plight with a mouthful of blood, 3 stitches and unbearable pain. *** ****** ************ ********** *** ************ ** *** ********* ** ** ***** *** ********** ***** ** **** ********
*** ********* ******* **** ***** *** ********* ** ******* ****** She offered to construct a dental bridge over the missing tooth. She further suggested that the 3 teeth that would support the bridge needed to undergo RCT. Consequently, she initiated the RCT *** ****** ***** ** ** ********* ******* ****** The RCT was primarily carried out by another person in her presence, *** *** ******* *** * ****** *** *** ***** ***** ******* *********** *** ******* *** *********** *** **** ** ****** *** **** ******** ************ *** *** ***** ******** *** *** *** ************* **** ***** ********* ** * ********* *******
reply_text: Dear S.Naskar: What I want more than anything is to address these issues with you personally. But you never gave that chance.Moreover it was a surgical extraction that may last upto an hour.The tooth was given a try for root canal treatment by 2 other dentists earlier that made it brittle and a hopeless case,some kind of discomfort is always expected with medical and dental treatment. You forgot to mention that the whole budget was about 22000INR out of which only 3000 INR had been deposited and your 80percent of the dental work is complete. Also, it is the team work that matters, so if the RCT was done by some other MDS doctor along with me, you should be bothered about the end-result .Also, it was done under my supervision.Since you had no time to stay back in Kolkata for more than 2 months,so an option of implant was ruled out,instead bridging option was suggested.

review: Good and well managed.  Had tooth extraction and till now it's going good. Good follow-up by support staffs

**** to  get an idea about which teeth is affected, she has done xray . and the funny thing is u wnt get a hard copy or report. she will mail u that photo. so basically u paid 300 for her reference. again u have to pay 300 as consultation. so till now 600 just to get an idea what is wrong . which i feel little expensive in a city like kolkata. ***** ** *** ********* *****  u cant spend 600 just for dental diagnosis. and she is asking 4000 just for capping and 6000 for 1 root canal.
now its upto you, if u r ready to spend that much.
reply_text: First of all,a digital Xray is the new technology Xray that carries least radiation exposure to the body of the patient as compared to analog Xray and secondly it does not come in a hard copy anywhere,,it has its best resolution in soft copy format,,so designed like that.Secondly the patient had a faulty root canal treatment done by some  other dentist 2 years,so it was difficult to arrive at a concrete conclusion as to which tooth was affected more--the already defective case done by earlier dentist or the adjacent tooth that too had a decay. Moreover ,step-by-step procedure was explained to the patient that would help him to get rid of  the existing problem.
